            <title><![CDATA[VS Code Setup]]></title>
            <guid>920f7595ecc74b9a991b39046da08888</guid>
            <pubDate>Thu, 05 Dec 2024 18:21:02 GMT</pubDate>
            <content:encoded><![CDATA[<h1 id="vs-code-setup"><a title="https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=PwGKhvqJCQM" href="https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=PwGKhvqJCQM">VS Code Setup</a></h1>
<p>This summarizes the steps describe in the above video by <a title="https://www.youtube.com/@ArjanCodes" href="https://www.youtube.com/@ArjanCodes">@ArjanCodes</a><br />
<a title="https://arjan.codes/designguide" href="https://arjan.codes/designguide">arjan.codes/designguide</a></p>
<p><a title="https://medium.com/@jonbackhaus/your-vs-code-project-needs-a-development-container-8643299f560c" href="https://medium.com/@jonbackhaus/your-vs-code-project-needs-a-development-container-8643299f560c">Your VS Code Project Needs A Development Container</a></p>
<h2 id="basecontainer">BaseContainer</h2>
<p>First attempt was ms std python devcontainer - nope<br />
Second attempt: <a title="https://medium.com/@shaliamekh/python-package-management-with-uv-for-dockerized-environments-f3d727795044" href="https://medium.com/@shaliamekh/python-package-management-with-uv-for-dockerized-environments-f3d727795044">create my own devcontainer</a></p>
<h2 id="auto-formatter">auto formatter</h2>
<ul>
<li>ruff
<ul>
<li>Either in OS or as VS Code extension</li>
<li>configure by <code>ruff.toml</code></li>
</ul>
</li>
<li>black (from microsofts python extension - is slower than ruff)</li>
</ul>
<h2 id="project-management">Project Management</h2>
<ul>
<li>poerty</li>
<li>uv</li>
</ul>
<h2 id="from-microsoft">from microsoft</h2>
<ul>
<li>python extension
<ul>
<li>include pylance (python intellisense)</li>
<li>includes python debugger</li>
</ul>
</li>
</ul>
<h2 id="misc">misc</h2>
<ul>
<li>Even better TOML</li>
<li><code>.vscode</code> folder
<ul>
<li><code>extensions.json</code>  can provide <code>"recommendations":[]</code>  which will be displayer in the <code>Recommended</code> section of the Extensions selection dialog (similar to <code>@recommended</code> search)</li>
</ul>
</li>
</ul>
<h2 id="howto">howto</h2>
<ol>
<li>create folder x ; cd into it</li>
<li><code>uv init</code> --no-workspace
<ul>
<li>we do not need a workspace for a single project</li>
</ul>
</li>
<li>create:
<ol>
<li><code>.vscode/</code></li>
<li><code>settings.json</code></li>
<li><code>extensions.json</code></li>
<li><code>.gitignore</code></li>
<li><code>src/</code></li>
<li>mv <code>hello.py</code> to <code>src/main.py</code></li>
<li><code>__init__.py</code></li>
<li><code>tests/</code></li>
<li><code>touch tests/test_main.py</code></li>
<li>$ uv add --dev pytest</li>
</ol>
</li>
</ol>
]]></content:encoded>
        </item>
